{"title_page": "List of ATP Tour Top-level tournament singles champions", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n[[Grand Slam (tennis)|Grand Slam]] tournaments, the [[ATP Tour Masters 1000|Masters series]] and the [[ATP Finals]] are considered the top-tier events of men's singles tennis since the introduction of the [[ATP Tour#ATP Tour|ATP Tour]] in [[1990 ATP Tour|1990]]. \n\nThe Association of Tennis Professionals defines them as follows:\n\n{{cquote|They are the biggest tournaments in our sport, where participation is mandatory, entry is reserved for the world\u2019s best and success is rewarded with fame and a rich haul of points and prize money.\n\nClaiming a title at each level \u2013 Grand Slam, Barclays ATP World Tour Finals and ATP World Tour Masters \u2013 has its unique challenges. But the tournaments are all stages upon which legends are made, where careers are defined and where victory earns players universal respect from peers, fans and media. Not surprisingly, the players with the best \u2018Big Titles\u2019 records are regarded as the giants of the game.<ref name=\"BigTitles\">[http://www.atpworldtour.com/en/news/federer-big-titles-2016 \"Big Titles: Federer Leads But Novak's Strike Rate Dazzles\"], ''[[Association of Tennis Professionals]]'', 10 May 2016.</ref>|ATP}}\n\nThis is a list of the men's singles champions at these events. The chart will help in visualizing how much a player accomplished amongst his peers in the course of an entire year.\n\n- Each entry has an asterisk (*) linking to the tournament of that year.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable nowrap\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:75%\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Year\n! colspan=\"4\"|[[Grand Slam (tennis)|Grand Slam tournaments]]<ref name=\"gsw\">{{cite web | url=https://www.atptour.com/en/scores/results-archive?tournamentType=gs | title=ATP Scores & Stats: Grand Slam tournaments}}</ref>\n! colspan=\"9\"|[[ATP World Tour Masters 1000|Masters Series]]<ref name=\"masters\">{{cite web | url=https://www.atptour.com/en/scores/results-archive?tournamentType=1000|title=ATP Scores & Stats: Masters tournaments}}</ref>\n! [[ATP World Tour Finals|ATP Finals]]<ref name=\"wtf\">{{cite web | url=https://www.nittoatpfinals.com/en/heritage/past-champions-and-cities | title=ATP Finals: Past champions}}</ref>\n! [[Tennis at the Summer Olympics|Olympics]]<ref name=\"ogm\">{{cite web | url=http://olympics.sporting99.com/track-field/tennis-mens-singles.html | title=Tennis Men's Singles Winners at Olympics}}</ref>\n|-\n! [[Australian Open|AO]]\n! [[French Open|FO]]\n! [[The Championships, Wimbledon|WIM]]\n! [[US Open (tennis)|USO]]\n! [[Indian Wells Masters|IW]]\n! [[Miami Masters|MI]]\n! [[Monte Carlo Masters|MC]]\n! [[Madrid Open (tennis)|MA]]/[[Hamburg Masters|HA]]\n! [[Rome Masters|RO]]\n! [[Canada Masters|CA]]\n! [[Cincinnati Masters|CI]]\n! [[Shanghai Masters (tennis)|SH]]/[[Madrid Open (tennis)|MA]]\n! [[Paris Masters|PA]]\n! YEC\n! OG\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''[[2020 ATP Tour|2020]]'''\n| style=\"background:#E6F2FF;\" | Djokovic[[2020 Australian Open \u2013 Men's Singles|*]]\n| style=\"background:#f9f0eb;\" | [[2020 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles|*]]\n| style=\"background:lightgray;\"| {{sort|zz|''Not held''}}{{efn|name=corona|Not held due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].}}\n| style=\"background:#E6F2FF;\" | [[2020 US Open \u2013 Men's Singles|*]] \n| style=\"background:lightgray;\" colspan=\"5\" | {{sort|zz|''Not held''}}{{efn|name=corona}}\n| style=\"background:#5F5F5;\" | [[2020 Rogers Cup \u2013 Men's Singles|*]]\n| style=\"background:#F5F5F5;\" | [[2020 Western & Southern Open \u2013 Men's Singles|*]]\n| style=\"background:#5F5F5;\" | [[2020 Rolex Shanghai Masters \u2013 Singles|*]]\n| style=\"background:#F5F5F5;\" | [[2020 Rolex Paris Masters \u2013 Singles|*]]\n| style=\"background:#FFFFE6;\" | [[2020 ATP World Tour Finals \u2013 Singles|*]]\n| style=\"background:#f5f5f5; color:#ccc;\u201c| {{sort|zz|Not he