{"title_page": "Shohei Moriyasu", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name=Shohei Moriyasu\n|image=\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|fullname=Shohei Moriyasu\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1991|8|17}}\n|birth_place=[[Hiroshima Prefecture|Hiroshima]], [[Japan]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|height={{Height|m=1.71}}\n|position=[[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n|currentclub=\n|clubnumber=\n|youthyears1=2007\u20132009|youthclubs1=[[Sanfrecce Hiroshima]]\n|youthyears2=2010\u20132013|youthclubs2=[[Hosei University]]\n|years1=2014\u20132015|clubs1=[[Kamatamare Sanuki]]|caps1=1|goals1=0\n|years2=2017\u2013|clubs2=[[Onehunga Sports]]|caps2=|goals2=\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=|managerclubs1=\n|medaltemplates=\n|club-update=\n|nationalteam-update=\n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Shohei Moriyasu'''|\u68ee\u4fdd \u7fd4\u5e73|Moriyasu Shohei|born August 17, 1991}} is a former [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[Association football|football]] player.<ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFIX04/?player_id=9327 J.League Data Site]{{in lang|ja}}</ref> His father is [[Hajime Moriyasu]], a former international football player and football manager. His brother [[Keigo Moriyasu|Keigo]] plays as a striker for [[Edgeworth FC]] in the [[National Premier Leagues Northern NSW]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ormond|first1=Aidan|title=YouTube sensation set for Cairns FFA Cup clash|url=http://www.theffacup.com.au/article/edgeworth-eagles-star-keigo-moriyasu-braced-for-fnq-heat-clash-in-ffa-cup/jclwlxm463v319mai7a5qitoc|website=FFA Cup|publisher=Football Federation Australia|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Playing career==\nShohei Moriyasu played for [[J2 League]] club; [[Kamatamare Sanuki]] from 2014 to 2015.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{J.League player|9327}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moriyasu, Shohei}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Hosei University alumni]]\n[[Category:Association football pe